<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><items termsofuse="https://boardgamegeek.com/xmlapi/termsofuse"><item type="boardgame" id="308264">
                                     				
				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Escalating Profs" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Escalating Profs is a cardgame in which your aim is to become the greatest scientiest in the world. Use insane experiments, ingenious ideas and shady sabatoga-tacticts to show everybody that you're the mastermind on the table!&amp;#10;Also you can combine the game with an App. So you have different modes to play. Like Sport, Quiz or Drink mode.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay:&amp;#10;Shuffle the deck and place it in the middle of the table. Every Player draws 7 handcards. Afterwards, everybody have to put 3 cards from the deck face down in front of her/him. These three cards represent the reputation of a player! Once per turn, you can put 1 CARD from your hand face down to your REPUTATION. (Always from left to right).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The number on the left upper corner of a card represents the PLAYING COST. &amp;#10;You can play as many CARDS per turn as you want, as long as the combined amount of  the PLAYING COST is not higher than your REPUTATION. You play one card after another, so use your mathematical skills to keep track of the total amout of PLAYING COSTS you already used.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After you played a CARD, you put it to the DISCARD PILE. (the DISCARD PILE is right next to your DECK). If you can&amp;acute;t or just don&amp;acute;t want to play another card, you finish your TURN by drawing 1 CARD from the DECK. Note that this is the last thing you can do. Therefore, immediately after drawing this card, the player next to your left side start his / her TURN.&amp;#10;IMPORTANT: After each TURN, the amount of used REPUTATION is put back to 0.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal of the Game:&amp;#10;If you increase your reputation to 10, you are the winner! Drops your reputation to 0, you must clear the table.&amp;#10;If your are the last 'Prof' standing, you're also the Winner!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
